But, the Chinese version of the phone are much cheaper, so I am wondering if I buy the Chinese one and just preinstall Google services or maybe I can just flash Hong Kong rom instead.

*   **Pros:** Cheaper than the Hong Kong version [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1).
*   **Cons:** Requires manual installation of Google services, which can be complex and may not always work perfectly [tradingshenzhen](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0). Some devices might not support Google installation [tradingshenzhen](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).

**Option 3: Buying the Chinese Version and Flashing the Hong Kong ROM**

*   **Pros:** Potentially gets you Google Play preinstalled [xdaforums](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5).
*   **Cons:** Risky process that can void your warranty [karamelcookies](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/3-0) [samsung](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/3-1). Can lead to data loss [xdaforums](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6) [droidwin](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/3-9) [justanswer](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/3-10). May cause a soft brick and compromise Knox security features if done incorrectly [xdaforums](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5). Chinese phones typically lack eSIM support, and flashing a Hong Kong ROM might not enable it [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/3-8) [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/3-4) [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/3-5).

**Recommendation:**

Given the information available as of July 16, 2025, I recommend trying **Option 2: Buying the Chinese Version and Installing Google Services Manually**, *before* considering flashing the ROM. Here's why:

3.  **Cost-Effective:** The Chinese version is likely cheaper [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1).

**Steps for Manual Google Services Installation:**

1.  **Purchase a Chinese Samsung Galaxy S23 Ultra.**
2.  **Enable "Install from Unknown Sources"** in your device's security settings [quora](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1).
3.  **Download a Google Installer app** or the Google Play Store APK from APKmirror.com [tradingshenzhen](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [quora](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1). 4.  **Install the Google apps and services.** Grant the necessary permissions [tradingshenzhen](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).
5.  **Use a VPN** during the installation process [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3).
6.  **Activate Google Services** in the phone's settings if necessary [tradingshenzhen](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).
7.  **Troubleshoot:** If you encounter issues, try uninstalling and reinstalling Google Play Services updates [quora](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5).
